  <description type="morphology">Stems green to purplish, with widely divergent or dichotomous branches, 7–40 cm, rigid, glan-dular-hairy at least distally. Leaf blades 0.5–2 cm, margins scar-ious near base, ciliate. Pedicels 1.5–3.5 mm. Flowers: calyx tube 10–14 × 0.8–1 mm, lobes 1–1.2 mm, base swollen, hardened; petals narrowly obovate, 11–16 mm, coronal appendages 0.4–0.6 mm. Capsules with rounded tip; carpophore 0.2–0.7 mm. Seeds in 1 row, with abrupt but round point, 1.3–1.8 mm. 2n = 28 (Europe).</description>
